description: For sale is a 17' foot Yarcraft 170 Patriot, deep V, fiberglass boat. Rated 130hp engine and 8 person capacity w/ max weight of 1745lbs . The boat has been completely rebuilt and painted from top to bottom and is better than new. There was no structural damage to this boat it just needed a lot of TLC. I have before and after photo's that I can share if interested. The entire boat was primed w/ marine grade epoxy primer and top coat painted w/ INTERLUX Perfection marine urethane paint. The bottom of the hull was top coated w/ Interlux VC performance epoxy paint. The bilge and transom interior was epoxy painted. The interior has all new marine grade carpet. The engine splash well is rhino lined to avoid staining and damage from fuel and oil as well as easy clean-up. All new marine grade wiring through out the boat w/ push to reset breakers for the main electricals. I also added 2 new battery mounting pads in the bow and accessory wiring for a trolling motor battery connection. There is terminal block in the helm console for accessory power connections. A new 1100pgh bilge pump. All stainless steel hardware. All new fuel line w/ fuel & water separating filter installed to the 18 gallon built in fuel tank. All new gauges in helm console. New U-flex steering system and cable. There is a one 6ft and one 8ft rod/storage compartment along the gunnels and 3 under seat storage compartments in the bow. 2 pedestal console seats. The drivers console seat has a adjustable pedestal. The Spartan roller trailer has been completely gone through. It has been primed and repainted. All new spindle bearings and seals installed, bearing buddies, 14" tires, 1 spare tire w/ rim, 2" tongue coupler, all new wiring, new lights, tongue jack and flat 4 wire harness plug. All this boat needs is a engine, engine controls and its ready to go. It was previously rigged w/ a 115hp and it moved out at approximately 45mph. I may be able to help you find a good used engine for this boat depending on what your looking for. I would also be willing to store the boat til May for the new owner if necessary. $4400 obo Call show contact info

description: I have a 19 foot Bayliner Trophy with a cuddy for sale. 120 Mercury Force main motor. This motor runs very well. I've maintained it well routinely changing spark plugs doing all maintenance and taking care of it well. 9.9 Mercury kicker motor. Right now it has a manual assist to lower and raise yet I've purchased a hydraulic assist I just haven't installed yet. I will include that in the price. I had made two years ago a custom cabin enclosure for her. All snaps are in perfect shape and it is super easy to put up and take down. The price of that was $2,500 alone. I also purchased a travel cover for it $500.00 new. The travel cover has one hole in it from a rod holder yet is in perfect condition otherwise. The cabin sleeps two and plenty of storage for all your gear. I also have a travel trailer and have purchased two brand new tires for it and have a full sized spare as well. The boat has a 50 gallon tank and I have a three gallon tank for the kicker. Two brand new batteries were installed last year as well. Top speed is 34 mph. I have a Lowrance HDS 8 Gen 2 which can be negotiated. I will throw in 2 Lowrance Elite 4 units in the price. I have used the boat mainly on Lake Superior and Lake Michigan and Lake of The Woods and Red Lake. This is a perfect trolling boat and pleasure cruiser. I have two Cannon Mag 10 STX electric down riggers which also can be negotiated. I also have over 20 Okuma and Magda line counter rods and reels and a lot of flasher and fly combos we could negotiate too. It's high quality gear. I'm selling the boat because I have a young family and don't get out much. The boat is slipped on Lake Superior at Connors Cove and you could have the slip for the remainder of the season for free. Call or text. I have plenty of pictures. Trolling salmon trout walleye fishing cabin
title: Bayliner Trophy with Cuddy
